Attributes

Const Name: AGX2K3K_ATTR_RANGE_CHECK
Description Name: Range Check
Type: ViBoolean
RangeTable: Boolean_values
Description: Specifies whether to validate attribute values and function parameters. If enabled, the instrument driver validates the parameter values that you pass to driver functions. Range checking parameters is very useful for debugging. After you validate your program, you can set this attribute to VI_FALSE to disable range checking and maximize performance.
The default value is VI_TRUE. Use the agx2k3k_InitWithOptions function to override this value.

Attribute Value: 1050002
Const Name: AGX2K3K_ATTR_QUERY_INSTRUMENT_STATUS
Description Name: Query Instrument Status
Type: ViBoolean
RangeTable: Boolean_values
Description: Specifies whether the instrument driver queries the instrument status after each operation. Querying the instrument status is very useful for debugging. After you validate your program, you can set this attribute to VI_FALSE to disable status checking and maximize performance
The instrument driver can choose to ignore status checking for particular attributes regardless of the setting of this attribute.
The default value is VI_FALSE. Use the agx2k3k_InitWithOptions function to override this value.

Attribute Value: 1050003
Const Name: AGX2K3K_ATTR_CACHE
Description Name: Cache
Type: ViBoolean
RangeTable: Boolean_values
Description: Specifies whether to cache the value of attributes. When caching is enabled, the instrument driver keeps track of the current instrument settings and avoids sending redundant commands to the instrument. Thus, you can significantly increase execution speed.
The instrument driver can choose always to cache or never to cache particular attributes regardless of the setting of this attribute.
The default value is VI_TRUE. Use the agx2k3k_InitWithOptions function to override this value.

Attribute Value: 1050004
Const Name: AGX2K3K_ATTR_SIMULATE
Description Name: Simulate
Type: ViBoolean
RangeTable: Boolean_values
Description: Specifies whether or not to simulate instrument driver I/O operations. If simulation is enabled, instrument driver functions perform range checking and call Ivi_GetAttribute and Ivi_SetAttribute functions, but they do not perform instrument I/O. For output parameters that represent instrument data, the instrument driver functions return calculated values.
The default value is VI_FALSE. Use the agx2k3k_InitWithOptions function to override this value.

Attribute Value: 1050005
Const Name: AGX2K3K_ATTR_RECORD_COERCIONS
Description Name: Record Value Coercions
Type: ViBoolean
RangeTable: Boolean_values
Description: Specifies whether the IVI engine keeps a list of the value coercions it makes for integer and real type attributes. You call agx2k3k Get Next Coercion Record to extract and delete the oldest coercion record from the list.
The default value is VI_FALSE. Use the agx2k3k_InitWithOptions function to override this value.

Attribute Value: 1050006
Const Name: AGX2K3K_ATTR_INTERCHANGE_CHECK
Description Name: Interchange Check
Type: ViBoolean
RangeTable: Boolean_values
Description: Specifies whether to perform interchangeability checking and retrieve interchangeability warnings.

The default value is VI_FALSE.

Interchangeability warnings indicate that using your application with a different instrument might cause different behavior. You call agx2k3k Get Next Interchange Warning to extract interchange warnings. Call the agx2k3k_ClearInterchangeWarnings function to clear the list of interchangeability warnings without reading them.
Interchangeability checking logs a warning for each attribute you have not set that affects the behavior of the instrument.

Attribute Value: 1050021
Const Name: AGX2K3K_ATTR_SPECIFIC_DRIVER_DESCRIPTION
Description Name: Description
Type: ViString
RangeTable:
Description: A string that contains a brief description of the specific driver.

Attribute Value: 1050514
Const Name: AGX2K3K_ATTR_SPECIFIC_DRIVER_PREFIX

Type: ViString
RangeTable:
Description: A string that contains the prefix for the instrument driver. The name of each user-callable function in this driver starts with this prefix.

Attribute Value: 1050510
Const Name: AGX2K3K_ATTR_LOGICAL_NAME
Description Name: Logical Name
Type: ViString
RangeTable:
Description: A string containing the logical name you specified when opening the current IVI session.
You may pass a logical name to the agx2k3k_init or agx2k3k_InitWithOptions functions. The IVI Configuration utility must contain an entry for the logical name. The logical name entry refers to a virtual instrument section in the IVI Configuration file. The virtual instrument section specifies a physical device and initial user options.

Attribute Value: 1050305
Const Name: AGX2K3K_ATTR_IO_RESOURCE_DESCRIPTOR
Description Name: I/O Resource Descriptor
Type: ViString
RangeTable:
Description: Indicates the resource descriptor the driver uses to identify the physical device.
If you initialize the driver with a logical name, this attribute contains the resource descriptor that corresponds to the entry in the IVI Configuration utility.
If you initialize the instrument driver with the resource descriptor, this attribute contains that value.

Attribute Value: 1050304
Const Name: AGX2K3K_ATTR_DRIVER_SETUP
Description Name: Driver Setup
Type: ViString
RangeTable:
Description: Some cases exist where you must specify instrument driver options at initialization time. An example of this is specifying a particular instrument model from among a family of instruments that the driver supports. This is useful when using simulation. You can specify driver-specific options through the DriverSetup keyword in the optionsString parameter to the agx2k3k_InitWithOptions function. If you open an instrument using a logical name, you can also specify the options through the IVI Configuration Utility.
The default value is an empty string.

Attribute Value: 1150020
Const Name: AGX2K3K_ATTR_ACQUISITION_START_TIME
Description Name: Acquisition Start Time
Type: ViReal64
RangeTable:
Description: Specifies the length of time from the trigger event to the first point in the waveform record. If the value is positive, the first point in the waveform record occurs after the trigger event. If the value is negative, the first point in the waveform record occurs before the trigger event.

SCPI Command:

Attribute Value: 1250109
Const Name: AGX2K3K_ATTR_HORZ_MIN_NUM_PTS
Description Name: Horz Min Num Pts
Type: ViInt32
RangeTable:
Description: Specifies the minimum number of points the end-user requires in the waveform record for each channel. The instrument driver uses the value the end-user specifies to configure the record length that the oscilloscope uses for waveform acquisition. If the instrument cannot support the requested record length, the driver shall configure the instrument to the closest bigger record length. The Horizontal Record Length attribute returns the actual record length.

SCPI Command:
:WAVeform:POINts <# points>

Attribute Value: 1250009
Const Name: AGX2K3K_ATTR_HORZ_RECORD_LENGTH
Description Name: Horz Record Length
Type: ViInt32
RangeTable:
Description: Returns the actual number of points the oscilloscope acquires for each channel. The value is equal to or greater than the minimum number of points the end-user specifies with the Horizontal Minimum Number of Points attribute.

Note: Oscilloscopes may use different size records depending on the value the user specifies for the Acquisition Type attribute.

SCPI Command:
:WAVeform:POINts <# points>

Attribute Value: 1250007
Const Name: AGX2K3K_ATTR_INITIATE_CONTINUOUS
Description Name: Initiate Continuous
Type: ViBoolean
RangeTable: Boolean_values
Description: Specifies whether the oscilloscope continuously initiates waveform acquisition. If the end-user sets this attribute to True, the oscilloscope immediately waits for another trigger after the previous waveform acquisition is complete. Setting this attribute to True is useful when the end-user requires continuous updates of the oscilloscope display. This specification does not define the behavior of the read waveform and fetch waveform functions when this attribute is set to True. The behavior of these functions is instrument specific.

SCPI Command:
:RUN
:SINGle

Attribute Value: 1250006

Type: ViReal64
RangeTable: attrProbeAttenuationRangeTable
Description: Specifies the scaling factor by which the probe the end-user attaches to the channel attenuates the input. For example, for a 10:1 probe, the end-user sets this attribute to 10.0.
Note that if the probe is changed to one with a different attenuation, and this attribute is not set, the amplitude calculations will be incorrect.

SCPI Command:

Attribute Value: 5
Const Name: AGX2K3K_ATTR_TRIGGER_HF_REJECT
Description Name: Trigger High Frequency Reject
Type: ViBoolean
RangeTable: Boolean_values
Description: Turns the high frequency reject filter off and on. The high frequency reject filter adds a 50 kHz low-pass filter in the trigger path to remove high frequency components from the trigger waveform. Use this filter to remove high- frequency noise, such as AM or FM broadcast stations, from the trigger path.

attrAcquisitionModeRangeTable
Discrete Value Actual Value Description
AGX2K3K_VAL_ACQ_MODE_REALTIME 0 Real time mode
AGX2K3K_VAL_ACQ_MODE_SEGMENT 1 Segmented mode.
AGX2K3K_VAL_ACQ_MODE_MREALTIME 3 same as Realtime except that in order to provide maximum update rate, the sample rate drops from 20 GSa/s to 2 GSa/s at a faster time/div setting than normal.
AGX2K3K_VAL_ACQ_MODE_EQUITIME 4 Equivalent time sampling mode
attrAcquisitionTypeRangeTable
Discrete Value Actual Value Description
AGX2K3K_VAL_NORMAL 0 Configures the oscilloscope to acquire one sample for each point in the waveform record. The oscilloscope uses real-time or equivalent time sampling.
AGX2K3K_VAL_PEAK_DETECT 1 Sets the oscilloscope to the peak-detect acquisition mode. The oscilloscope oversamples the input signal and keeps the minimum and maximum values that correspond to each position in the waveform record. The oscilloscope uses only real-time sampling.
AGX2K3K_VAL_AVERAGE 4 Configures the oscilloscope to acquire multiple waveforms and calculate the average value for each point in the waveform record. The end-user specifies the number of waveforms to acquire with the Number of Averages attribute. The oscilloscope uses real-time or equivalent time sampling.
AGX2K3K_VAL_HI_RES 2 Configures the oscilloscope to oversample the input signal. The oscilloscope calculates the average value that corresponds to each position in the waveform record. The oscilloscope uses only real-time sampling.

attrMathWindowRangeTable
Discrete Value Actual Value Description
AGX2K3K_VAL_MATH_WINDOW_HANNING 0 Useful for frequency resolution and general purpose use. It is good for resolving two frequencies that are close together, or for making frequency measurements. This is the default window.
AGX2K3K_VAL_MATH_WINDOW_FLATTOP 1 Best for making accurate amplitude measurements of frequency peaks.
AGX2K3K_VAL_MATH_WINDOW_RECTANGULAR 2 Useful for transient signals, and signals where there are an integral number of cycles in the time record.
AGX2K3K_VAL_MATH_WINDOW_BLACKMAN_HARRIS 3 Reduces time resolution compared to the rectangular window, but it improves the capacity to detect smaller impulses due to lower secondary lobes (provides minimal spectral leakage).

attrRuntPolarityRangeTable
Discrete Value Actual Value Description
AGX2K3K_VAL_RUNT_POSITIVE 1 The oscilloscope triggers on a positive runt. A positive runt occurs when a rising edge crosses the low runt threshold and does not cross the high runt threshold before re-crossing the low runt threshold.
AGX2K3K_VAL_RUNT_NEGATIVE 2 The oscilloscope triggers on a negative runt. A negative runt occurs when a falling edge crosses the high runt threshold and does not cross the low runt threshold before re-crossing the high runt threshold.
AGX2K3K_VAL_RUNT_EITHER 3 The oscilloscope triggers on either a positive or negative runt.

funcHistogramMeasureRangeTable
Discrete Value Actual Value Description
AGX2K3K_VAL_BWIDTH 1 the width of each bin (bucket) in the histogram
AGX2K3K_VAL_HITS 2 the sum of all hits in all bins (buckets) in the histogram
AGX2K3K_VAL_M1S 3 the percentage of histogram hits that lie within +/-1 Std Dev of the mean
AGX2K3K_VAL_M2S 4 the percentage of histogram hits that lie within +/-2 Std Dev of the mean
AGX2K3K_VAL_M3S 5 the percentage of histogram hits that lie within +/-3 Std Dev of the mean
AGX2K3K_VAL_MAX 6 the value corresponding to the maximum bin that has any hits
AGX2K3K_VAL_MEAN 7 the mean value of the histogram
AGX2K3K_VAL_MED 8 the median value of the histogram
AGX2K3K_VAL_MIN 9 the value corresponding to the minimum bin that has any hits
AGX2K3K_VAL_MODE 10 the mode value of the histogram
AGX2K3K_VAL_PEAK 11 the maximum number of hits in any single bin
AGX2K3K_VAL_PPEAK 12 the delta between the Max and Min values
AGX2K3K_VAL_SDEV 13 the standard deviation of the histogram values

funcFixedOptionRangeTable
Discrete Value Actual Value Description
AGX2K3K_VAL_FIXED_AUTO 1 The clock is recovered using the signal edge database only.
AGX2K3K_VAL_FIXED_SEMI 2 The clock is recovered using the expected nominal data rate as a seed and the signal edge database.
